import React, { useEffect } from 'react'; import L from 'leaflet'; import 'leaflet/dist/leaflet.css'; import './Landing.css'; // your React component code here const Landing = () => { useEffect(() => { // Leaflet map setup (runs once after component mounts) if (!L) return; const southWest = L.latLng(1.144, 103.535); const northEast = L.latLng(1.494, 104.502); const maxBounds = L.latLngBounds(southWest, northEast); const map = L.map('mapdiv', { center: L.latLng(1.2868108, 103.8545349), zoom: 16, }); map.setMaxBounds(maxBounds); const basemap = L.tileLayer('https://www.onemap.gov.sg/maps/tiles/Default/{z}/{x}/{y}.png', { detectRetina: true, maxZoom: 19, minZoom: 11, attribution: ' OneMap © contributors | Singapore Land Authority', }); basemap.addTo(map); // Cleanup map on unmount return () => { map.remove(); }; }, []); return ( <> {/* Meta and CSS are normally in public/index.html for React apps */}
